6
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:38,240
Where the fuck are you going?
Where's the money?

7
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:40,480
-Where the fuck is my money?
-I messed up.

8
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:43,720
I don't have it anymore.
I'll give it back, I swear.

9
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,360
Please.

10
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,960
I warned you!

11
00:01:56,040 --> 00:02:00,480
What are you doing?
What did you see? John Wayne?

12
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,920
You're Black too.
How can you be John Wayne?

13
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,200
Leave him alone. We need him, not you!

14
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,080
He's collaborative.

15
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:12,160
Is it true that you're collaborative?
Yes or no?

16
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,800
-Yes.
-See? You're good.

17
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:15,680
Good.

18
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,440
Hello?

19
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:29,040
Call the guy, Dad. Tell him it's all good.

20
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,040
Are you sure?

21
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:33,720
There's a Black guy who'll take the blame.
Give a little money to his wife and son.

22
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:34,680
All right.

23
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:37,080
God sees and provides.

24
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,000
-Bye.
-Bye, son. Bye.

25
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,880
SARA - WOMAN IN THE SHADOWS

26
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:54,800
ANTONIO CARDARELLI EMERGENCY ROOM

27
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:17,040
You like my car, huh?
Do you need some spare parts?

28
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:20,240
I want to save you some trouble.

29
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:23,720
No need to appear every time
like the Virgin Mary.

30
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,760
I get it.

31
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,920
-You get what?
-Well…

32
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:32,000
You can usually find information
on pensioners doing favors for friends.

33
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:35,920
But nothing on you.
It's like you don't exist.

34
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,960
Good job.

35
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:39,800
But you must've also figured out
it's better if I don't exist, right?

36
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:40,840
Of course.

37
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,160
If the coroner asks who you are,

38
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,680
what the fuck should I tell him?
That you're a ghost?

39
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,800
If we don't go in,
you don't have to tell him anything.

40
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,400
Why me of all people?

41
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,600
You haven't worked a real case
in four years.

42
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:01,720
Ever since your all-too-evident honesty

43
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:04,280
led you to step on the toes
of someone bigger than you.

44
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:08,200
So you got a nice promotion
to the crappiest office in the station,

45
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:10,920
where, except for
the occasional substitution,

46
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,680
like the night my son died,
you're rotting away.

47
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,440
Inevitably losing, day by day,

48
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:20,520
your identity as a good investigator.

49
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,680
Fine.

50
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,160
So let's say I work with you.

51
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:29,160
And you and your friends
get me back on the mobile unit.

52
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,120
No.

53
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:34,080
You don't work with me. You work for me.

54
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,520
MORGUE

55
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:48,040
It's weird. Not only are the causes
of death different,

56
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,800
but the times don't match.

57
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:53,560
Gaspare Russo was shot
three times in the chest.

58
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,040
One, two and three.

59
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:59,280
When the two bodies were found,
he'd been dead for about three hours.

60
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:02,600
But not the kid.
He'd been dead a lot longer.

61
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,640
You could say he was unlucky.

62
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,960
-Meaning?
-Follow me.

63
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:11,840
Sergio Minucci had a rare spleen disease
that made it extremely vulnerable.

64
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:15,080
A single blow, not even a very hard one,

65
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:19,000
caused it to rupture
and the slow hemorrhage that killed him.

66
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,280
How slow?

67
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,080
From the bruises and lesions,

68
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:27,280
I'd say the beating occurred
36 hours earlier, 48 at the most.

69
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:32,280
The kid was beaten and tied up,
as you can see from the wrist marks

70
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:36,200
and the ankle marks,
and left for dead where he was found.

71
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:39,960
-Okay. Thanks a lot.
-Don't mention it, Pardo.

72
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,720
He got beaten, but not in the face.

73
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:49,800
-He wasn't supposed to die.
-So what do you think? Intimidation?

74
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,640
Information, more than anything.

75
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:57,240
Care to tell me why, or do I have to wait
for the next apparition?

76
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,600
They ransacked his house.

77
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:02,400
Someone wanted to know something,
and he didn't talk.

78
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:06,400
I don't know why I want to humiliate
myself by asking you this,

79
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:08,720
when I know you'll never answer, but…

80
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:13,560
If you and your friends are handling this,
maybe you have ties with the kid, right?

81
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:16,080
Couldn't that be the key?

82
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:20,440
Maybe whoever kidnapped him
wanted information about you?

83
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:26,520
Let's start with Gaspare Russo.
Who was he? What were his ties to the kid?

84
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:29,080
Why did they leave them
next to each other?

85
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,160
Okay.

86
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:32,400
I work for you now. What do I have to do?

87
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:35,320
How should I know? You're the cop.

88
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,120
POLICE

89
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,440
According to our colleagues,

90
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:46,520
Gaspare Russo supervised
illegal immigrants' work.

91
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,800
But he was low-rank. A small fish.

92
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:53,120
-Boris! Hi!
-Musella! So?

93
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,360
The weird thing is,

94
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:57,880
forensics say that Russo sent
a voice message to his wife from the car

95
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,760
saying he was going home.

96
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:02,160
Only, he died and the car disappeared.

97
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:05,560
Anyway, it's all in here,
car papers included.

98
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,120
Is everything okay?

99
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:10,720
What?

100
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:14,080
You suddenly took leave
without telling me.

101
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,400
And you've got Boris.

102
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,800
-I took some leave to be with my dog.
-Fine.

103
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:21,200
-It's none of your business anyway.
-Absolutely.

104
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:23,840
-Go inside. Thanks.
-You're welcome, Inspector.

105
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,560
Boris. No, Boris! Hey!

106
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,440
Thanks for the lift.

107
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:41,200
I had to finish some work.
I never would've made it getting the bus.

108
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,480
What do you do,
if you don't mind me asking?

109
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:49,920
I do check-ins for vacation rentals,

110
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,400
wedding photos, loser actors' portfolios.

111
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,600
Shit like that.

112
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:56,640
In theory, I'm a photographer. In theory.

113
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,600
-Is it much farther?
-No.

114
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,640
I mean, is it here?

115
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,720
I know, the place sucks, but he's good.

116
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,440
Morning, Nino.

117
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,160
Nino.

118
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:30,040
I didn't do anything, Inspector.
I didn't do anything.

119
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:33,880
Where are you going?

120
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,320
Hey!

121
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:39,360
Will you stop? Hey!

122
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,560
Damn…

123
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,000
Again, sir?

124
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:47,640
-I'm not arresting you. Will you shut up?
-What do you want, then?

125
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,800
I need some information.

126
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,880
-Information?
-Yeah.

127
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:00,040
I need to find this car.

128
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,240
Can you help me?

129
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:05,360
-Park there.
-Here?

130
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,280
Yeah.

131
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:11,200
BONELLI FOR A NEW CAMPANIA

132
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:27,760
DOCTOR'S OFFICE

133
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,120
God. You get more beautiful by the day.

134
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,640
-Hi.
-Hi.

135
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:35,560
-Fusco, pleasure to meet you.
-Sara Morozzi. You too.

136
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:36,920
Come on.

137
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:44,000
Who's that? A relative?

138
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:46,160
No, an acquaintance who gave me a ride.

139
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:49,280
Okay, got it. Come in, take a seat.

140
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,520
Excuse me.

141
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:15,920
PROPERTY - THE CAMPANIA CHALLENGE
LEGALITY, NUCLEAR ENERGY, BUSINESS

142
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,240
Hello? Good morning.

143
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:37,000
I wanted to know if Mr. Tarallo

144
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:41,360
will hold a press conference
for the death of his aide, Sergio Minucci.

145
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,840
BODY SHOP

146
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,560
PARKING LOT
EXIT

147
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,920
-The mechanic sent me.
-Oh, it's you?

148
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,520
Where's the car?

149
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:20,600
It's in here. Want me to take you?

150
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:22,960
Give me the money.

151
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,160
See you later, man.

152
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,080
Here's Gaspare Russo.

153
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:29,960
Hey, Musella.

154
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:33,640
I found Russo's car.
I'm sending you a pin.

155
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:37,440
No. Musè, listen.

156
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:40,080
You take the credit for finding the car.

157
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:43,560
Have forensics analyze it
and let me know when there's news. Okay?

158
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,760
Where did you find that doctor?

159
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:52,760
He was smoking in the studio.

160
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:55,960
-Can't we choose another one?
-He watched Giorgio grow up.

161
00:12:56,720 --> 00:13:00,520
He's his best friend's dad.
Your son spent his teens with them.

162
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:04,080
They're the first people I met
after we started dating.

163
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:09,120
His father, your ex-husband,
had been dead a while.

164
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:14,560
He said they were both crazy,
and they had lots of fun together.

165
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,200
They were the family he never had.

166
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,360
-We're here.
-What is this place?

167
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,720
It's my place.

168
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:14,160
OBSTETRIC ULTRASOUND

169
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,280
I used to take Giorgio here.

170
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:07,560
It's really ugly,
but it was paradise for us.

171
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:14,400
He gave me a massage every night.

172
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:18,360
But that's not the only reason I miss him.

173
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:22,920
I miss the things he didn't do too.
I miss everything about him.

174
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:29,240
How old were you when you got pregnant?

175
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,400
He didn't even tell you that?

176
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,480
I was your age.

177
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:38,200
He never mentioned you.

178
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:43,680
One day we were talking
about the baby and…

179
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:48,720
about possible resemblances.

180
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:55,040
-He only told me that--
-He hoped the baby wouldn't look like me.

181
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,760
So I asked him what had happened.

182
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:04,160
He just told me you left
and forgot about him. That's it.

183
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,000
Do you think you can forget that?

184
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,240
If my mom's right,
and you're a criminal, yes.

185
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,720
But that's not what you think.

186
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:23,240
The bench you sat on
the first time you were waiting for me

187
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,760
was Giorgio's favorite.

188
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:28,600
But you couldn't know that.

189
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,440
I think that…

190
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:39,360
there's something bigger,
more powerful, that goes beyond us.

191
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,240
That's what I think.

192
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,400
Listen, I have to go.

193
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:57,400
If you don't mind, I'll go with a friend.

194
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:59,720
-No. I can drive you if you--
-No.

195
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,840
If you want…

196
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:08,000
we can meet again, even tonight,
maybe on that same bench.

197
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:12,640
I never thought I'd say this,
but it's good for me.

198
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,320
Maybe. I don't know.

199
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,800
All I know is I go crazy at home.

200
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:38,240
-Hey, Musella.
-I owe you one, Inspector.

201
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:42,040
They're all congratulating me.
Even the mobile unit couldn't believe it.

202
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:45,760
Okay, Musella. Get to the point.
I'm in a hurry. I'm busy.

203
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:50,240
Yes. Russo's car is covered
in fingerprints of a Nigerian felon,

204
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:52,160
a guy named Kamil Usman.

205
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,840
I sent a picture to your phone.

206
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:56,920
He's in Castel Volturno.
They're going to get him right now.

207
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,160
Okay. Thanks, Musella. Thanks.

208
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:02,360
Hey, enjoy the celebration.

209
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:04,600
-Thanks, Inspector.
-Bye.

210
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,840
I'll show you.

211
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,320
You fucking know-it-all.

212
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,440
-Pardo.
-Morozzi.

213
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:25,640
One of my informants told me
there were fingerprints

214
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:30,880
inside Gaspare Russo's car
belonging to a Nigerian named Kamil Usman.

215
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:31,920
Oh good.

216
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:35,640
-That's it?
-Want me to congratulate you?

217
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:37,800
Of course not. Never mind.

218
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:40,400
Come on.
The press conference is about to start.

219
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:43,440
-Coming. I'll be right there.
-Okay, bye.

220
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:45,640
What the fuck?

221
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:06,160
MORE SECURITY, MORE FREEDOM
I'M WITH TARALLO

222
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:09,040
Good morning, everyone.

223
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,560
I just talked with the police chief,

224
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:17,520
and we caught the man
who killed Gaspare Russo,

225
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:21,240
a supervisor on the tomato fields,
and our Sergio.

226
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,840
His name is…

227
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:27,120
Kamil Usman.

228
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:31,040
Turns out he's an illegal immigrant.

229
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:36,200
He was arrested a short time ago.
He didn't resist and…

230
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:38,080
he confessed.

231
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:42,320
Sergio was probably in that area,

232
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:46,000
as he often was,
because he was a researcher.

233
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:47,960
He was someone who took initiative.

234
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:51,840
I'm sorry.

235
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:56,560
That's what I liked about him.

236
00:19:57,400 --> 00:20:01,320
After all, illegal farm work
is one of the many plagues on our country,

237
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:05,520
but especially in our region, Campania.

238
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:13,160
It's likely that Gaspare Russo
and Kamil Usman saw Sergio,

239
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:18,320
and something that was meant to be
a lesson or a just scare,

240
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,760
turned into a murder.

241
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:22,960
We lost a friend.

242
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:26,440
I… lost a friend.

243
00:20:26,520 --> 00:20:31,360
My aides were so worried,
to the point they thought I might give up.

244
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:34,320
I want to take the opportunity
at this press conference

245
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,600
to assure everyone.

246
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,360
I won't give up.

247
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:42,160
I have no intention of giving up.
I owe it to Sergio.

248
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:46,400
And we'll keep fighting for our only goal.

249
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:50,880
"More freedom, more security." That's it.

250
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:58,880
Can you explain
what a 30-year-old member of your staff

251
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:01,760
was really doing
