Even though you're still an asshole.

504
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:56,800
And you're still a bitch.

505
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:10,480
As he was finishing recording the message,
he drove over a manhole.

506
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:18,240
Not enough background noise
for him to be in the city.

507
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:22,560
I'd say he was driving
on a secondary road.

508
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:25,120
No. In the country.

509
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:31,840
Kamil Usman confessed
that he and Gaspare Russo killed Sergio.

510
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:37,040
Then he argued with Russo
and killed him as well.

511
00:40:37,760 --> 00:40:41,640
Then he got rid of the bodies
in the place where they were found.

512
00:40:41,720 --> 00:40:43,760
That's correct, yeah.

513
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:44,880
But it's false.

514
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:48,400
Because Gaspare Russo
was killed right there.

515
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:55,320
He wasn't with them before.
He ended up there by accident, not Sergio.

516
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:59,160
What we know is that Gaspare Russo
sent a voice message to his wife

517
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:01,240
just before he got killed.

518
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:02,560
He was driving.

519
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:05,000
Filomè, are you sleeping?

520
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:08,120
You could've called me, you know?

521
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:12,280
Anyway, I'm already in the car.
I'll be home in five minutes.

522
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,320
Okay? See you there. Take care.

523
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:23,000
He ended up just a few hundred meters
from where the bodies were found.

524
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:24,920
Who's this guy?

525
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,360
Let him get out of the car.

526
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:31,720
He got out of the car, and they shot him.

527
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:35,440
Hey, what happened? What are you doing?

528
00:41:37,760 --> 00:41:40,520
What does the Nigerian
have to do with Sergio?

529
00:41:40,600 --> 00:41:42,400
Exactly. What's he have to do with him?

530
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:45,080
I mean, why did Kamil lie
about what happened?

531
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:47,000
Like he wanted to take the blame.

532
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:50,800
Why did he take the blame
for someone else?

533
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:53,600
It's important.

534
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:56,160
Oh, nice.

535
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:00,960
So…

536
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:04,600
renting and renovating this house

537
00:42:04,680 --> 00:42:07,240
was your last attempt to not get dumped?

538
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:10,320
It was him. Boris.

539
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:16,560
Let's go get some air.

540
00:42:17,320 --> 00:42:18,160
Not you.

541
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:19,920
You later, okay?

542
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:39,720
If you wanted to go for a walk,
you could've said so.

543
00:42:40,240 --> 00:42:42,760
I know a couple of places
that are nicer than this.

544
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:45,480
Relax. You don't look like a cop.

545
00:42:46,120 --> 00:42:48,080
-Oh, you're being ironic?
-Yeah.

546
00:42:48,160 --> 00:42:52,160
You should've been a comedian.
I piss myself laughing whenever you speak.

547
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,000
You do the honors.

548
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:00,840
Thanks.

549
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:04,080
-That's her.
-Yeah.

550
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:06,640
Ma'am?

551
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:08,360
Ma'am…

552
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:12,600
We're off to a good start, huh?
Ma'am, open the door.

553
00:43:12,680 --> 00:43:17,720
Ma'am, we don't want to harm you.
The gate was open, ma'am.

554
00:43:18,720 --> 00:43:22,280
Hey, open the door! We're from…

555
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:25,800
-If it's obvious, what's the difference?
-Stay back.

556
00:43:26,320 --> 00:43:27,960
Ma'am, don't be afraid.

557
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:30,160
I'm Sara, a friend of Kamil's.

558
00:43:31,600 --> 00:43:34,000
We're looking for Kamil and his family.

559
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:39,240
Maybe you can help me. Huh?
I just want to talk for a few minutes.

560
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:40,840
Can you open the door?

561
00:43:44,760 --> 00:43:46,000
Just you and me.

562
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:53,080
Not him.

563
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:54,560
Not him.

564
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:07,280
Kamil Usman is in debt.

565
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:11,400
Even to the husband of that woman
who he had to give his house to.

566
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:13,560
The house? That's a house?

567
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:18,560
Then he got arrested…
for a crime he confessed to.

568
00:44:18,640 --> 00:44:22,200
But the dynamic in his confession
doesn't line up with the facts.

569
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:24,960
The police don't get it,
he remains in prison,

570
00:44:25,040 --> 00:44:28,280
still in debt, I guess,
and his wife and son leave.

571
00:44:28,360 --> 00:44:30,400
Yeah. With what money?

572
00:44:32,080 --> 00:44:37,160
The money he earned by taking the blame
for the death of Sergio and Gaspare Russo.

573
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:41,920
Gaspare Russo just happened to be there
at the wrong time.

574
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:45,200
The two deaths are not linked.
We only lost time.

575
00:44:45,880 --> 00:44:47,560
Someone linked them later.

576
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:51,720
The same person who paid Kamil
to take all the blame

577
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:54,440
and wanted us to find his car so easily.

578
00:44:54,520 --> 00:44:57,440
Otherwise, why didn't Kamil
torch it or sink it in the sea?

579
00:44:58,640 --> 00:44:59,760
See? You're not dumb.

580
00:45:01,560 --> 00:45:03,320
Some good news every now and then.

581
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:07,760
-So we have to start over?
-No. Why?

582
00:45:08,960 --> 00:45:09,840
Who is it?

583
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:11,800
Viola.

584
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:14,680
Viola.

585
00:45:14,760 --> 00:45:16,800
So, Sergio was doing something weird.

586
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:20,240
Exactly once a week,
he'd write in the same group

587
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:21,880
that he was looking for a house.

588
00:45:21,960 --> 00:45:26,560
Same formula, but different areas
and different kinds of houses.

589
00:45:26,640 --> 00:45:30,000
It doesn't make sense
for someone who's looking for a house,

590
00:45:30,080 --> 00:45:31,840
unless they're schizophrenic.

591
00:45:31,920 --> 00:45:33,400
You never met my ex.

592
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:35,200
It's a code.

593
00:45:36,680 --> 00:45:39,880
I asked Viola to do research
because I noticed some coincidences.

594
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,080
His last post mentions the address
of the museum he visited before dying.

595
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:46,280
Look.

596
00:45:46,360 --> 00:45:50,040
Isn't that the address
of the Museo delle Reliquie? Scroll down.

597
00:45:50,120 --> 00:45:52,400
Isn't that where Museo del Castello is?

598
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:53,920
Yeah.

599
00:45:54,440 --> 00:45:58,160
It was a way for Sergio
to set up a safe meeting in a museum

600
00:45:58,240 --> 00:46:00,720
that he indicated
through the fake house search?

601
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:01,800
Exactly.

602
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:05,960
Could you post a new ad as if he did it?

603
00:46:06,040 --> 00:46:06,920
Yes.

604
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:11,000
We'll go to the meeting
and find out who he secretly met with.

605
00:46:11,600 --> 00:46:12,920
At the Donnaregina?

606
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:14,720
-Yes.
-What should I write?

607
00:46:15,520 --> 00:46:22,520
"Urgently looking for a spacious house
on Donnaregina Street."

608
00:46:23,400 --> 00:46:25,160
"Tenant has references

609
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:29,200
and intends to continue
the activity carried out so far."

610
00:46:31,360 --> 00:46:32,800
-Should I post it?
-Yes.

611
00:46:34,880 --> 00:46:38,120
-I have to go now, but I'll let you know.
-Thank you.

612
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:40,000
-Bye, Pardo.
-Bye.

613
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:52,240
Was it really necessary to involve her?

614
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:54,920
Necessary, no. Useful, yes.

615
00:46:57,600 --> 00:47:00,720
Do you think we'll find
Sergio's real killer at the museum?

616
00:47:00,800 --> 00:47:02,440
Let's see if they take the bait.

617
00:47:04,680 --> 00:47:07,160
Who killed Sergio
is not important anymore.

618
00:47:08,080 --> 00:47:10,120
What's important is who's behind it.

619
00:47:10,640 --> 00:47:13,400
The situation is more serious
than I imagined.

